      <h1 class='title'>Regulatory Impact Assessments</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 04 November 2004 vol 666 c12WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_12ws' title='Col. 12WS &mdash; HL Deb 04 November 2004 vol 666 c12WS' name='column_12ws' href='#column_12ws' rel='bookmark'>12WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0666P0-09614'>
        <a name='S5LV0666P0_20041104_LWS_5'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-bassam' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0666P0_20041104_LWS_5' title='Link to this speech by Mr John Bassam' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-john-bassam" title="Mr John Bassam">Lord Bassam of Brighton</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0666P0-09614">The Government are committed to ensuring that regulations are necessary, give effective protection, balance cost and risk, are fair and command public confidence. In accordance with this, we require departments to produce and publish regulatory impact assestments (RIAs) for all regulatory proposals likely to have an impact on business, charities or voluntary bodies. Since 1 April 2004, RIAs have also been carried out on proposals with a significant impact on the public sector.</p><p id="S5LV0666P0-09615">I have today presented to Parliament a Command Paper (Cm 6329) listing RIAs published between 1 January and 30 June 2004. Copies of those listed have been placed in the Libraries of both Houses. This is the 21st such Command Paper.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
